§l     Agents of 
       Chaos§r§r§r§r

       Vol I: +,+ 
#- §lAbout this book§r:

Agents of Chaos is intended to allow the reader to get a brief understanding of the world's provocateurs and formentors of anarchy, not to explain the pathologies of the parties involved. This introductory volume focuses upon the +,+
#- and readers are highly encouraged to contribute to the upkeep of the Agents of Chaos series by correspondance. 
#- §4§lNew Danzilona Federation§r: The residents of New Danzilona are an unpleasant combination of capitalists, nationalists, and anarchists. Their form of government is too weak to provide for the proper upkeep of the state and has resulted in numerous 
#- §4instances of citizen led militias forming without government oversight or control.  
As a result, the state has found itself powerless to stop leaderless armies from entangling the Federation in severl unjustifiable conflicts. 
If this was the only 
#- §4problem with the New Danzilon Federation, it would not be the major formentor of unrest and instability that it is. The second and arguably far more destructive flaw in the Danzilonan national character is their particularly noxious form of so-called 
#- §4democracy. The Federation's system of elections and seperation of power encourages the rise of demogogues and firebrands. Military pacts are the national pastime of a nation ruled by summer soldiers and self styled soldiers of fortune. These pacts 
#- §4are irresponsible in the extreme and encourage even more unstable states to attempt to resolve disputes by force of arms rather than arbitration. There has hardly been a war where a militia with a name that sounds highly official hasn't dragged the 
#- §4Federation into a misguided war. It is because of this misguided obsession with martial glory that the New Danzilona Federation has yet to actually achieve any military wins without help from more organized and capable allies. 
#- §§§§§6§lMount Augusta§r§6: Perhaps the greatest cauldron of chaos to ever exist in the +,+ for any sustained period of time. The social structure of Mount Augusta is little more than peaceful anarchy at best, and often the scene of streetfights and faux 
#- §6military conflicts that tarnish the image of the government and contribute to political extremism by way of normalizing the most severe political conditions in the social culture of the town. The lack of government authority and low requirements for 
#- §6citizenship have created a refugee filled state where the political scene is dominated by emotions rather than logic, loot rather than profits, and flash rather than substance. 
#- §5§lU3P§r§5: The United Provinces is a +,+ alliances that is ostensibly dedicated to fostering economic growth and civil relations in the quadrant. In practice, it has been a primary atagonist to any growth except its own, using the threat of blockades to
#- §5to choke off any economic development not sanctioned by its ruling body. This has interfered with free trade and negatively impacted the development of the rail system in the +,+ as non U3P towns are effectively blacklisted from the U3P trade network 
#- §5unless their leaders agree to secret treaties offering the U3P tribute, political concessions, or economic power.
#- §9§lRiverford§r§9: A more openly jingoistic and imperial town has yet to be seen in the quadrant. Riverford was the embodiment of New Danzilona's desire to turn its martial dreams into a twisted reality. Riverford was a colony of the NDZ that savagely 
#- §9attacked the small town of Vird when its residents refused to leave their lands that they had inhabited before Riverford was even founded. Riverford's sole purpose was to give Danzilona's ultranationalists a way to kill and take land without officially 
#- §9officially declaring war. When Riverford was finally confronted about its aggression, New Danzilona revealed itself to be behind the spree of wars by sending a so-called private militia force to assist Riverford's attempt to take over yet more land.
#- This book deals only with state level actors that have consistently tried to destabilize the hard earned prosperity of the +,+ out of a misguided belief that the key to political power is by the creation of failed states. The ample amounts of evidence 
#- detailing the sponsorship of terrorism by several prominent citizens of New Danzilona, Mount Augusta, U3P and other cities in the +,+ has been omitted from publication in this book due to the specific area covered by this volume of Agents of Chaos. 
#- §lContact§r; Readers who wish to contact the author are encouraged to do so by leaving mail at the Prussian University or by delivering messages via book or written media to the author's home in Breslau, Kingdom Of Prussia.
